	<title>
		<paragraph x="12" y="+4" width="605" height="0" style="headline" tabs="0" indent="0"><![CDATA[<B><TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="12" COLOR="#000000" LETTERSPACING="0" KERNING="0"><B>Look at the pie chart and complete the report by filling each gap with the past simple of the verb given in brackets.</B></FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT></B>]]></paragraph>
	</title>
	<body>
		<paragraph type="text" x="100" y="+176" width="500" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000" LETTERSPACING="0" KERNING="0">In 1961 people in the UK mostly [1] (watch) television or [2] (listen) to the radio in their leisure time. On average they [3] (spend) almost half of their free time on these activities. After that [4](come) other unspecified pastimes, which [5] (take up) about an hour and a quarter a day. People [6] (not seem) to socialise a great deal, as this [7] (account) for only 35 minutes in a typical day. People [8] (eat) out, [9] (go) to the cinema or [10] (entertain) themselves in other ways outside the home for an average of 28 minutes a day. Finally, people [11] (play) sports or [12] (walk) for an average of only 9 minutes a day.</FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
		<paragraph height="0" width="605" y="+16" x="12"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT SIZE="2"></FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
		<field id="1" group="1" type="i:gap" mode="0">
			<answer correct="true">watched </answer>
		</field>
		<field mode="0" type="i:gap" group="2" id="2">
			<answer correct="true">listened </answer>
		</field>
		<field id="3" group="3" type="i:gap" mode="0">
			<answer correct="true">spent </answer>
		</field>
		<field id="4" group="4" type="i:gap" mode="0">
			<answer correct="true">came </answer>
		</field>
		<field id="5" group="5" type="i:gap" mode="0">
			<answer correct="true">took up </answer>
		</field>
		<field id="6" group="6" type="i:gap" mode="0">
			<answer correct="true">did not seem </answer>
			<answer correct="true">didn't seem</answer>
			<answer correct="true">seemed not</answer>
		</field>
		<field id="7" group="7" type="i:gap" mode="0">
			<answer correct="true">accounted </answer>
		</field>
		<field id="8" group="8" type="i:gap" mode="0">
			<answer correct="true">ate </answer>
		</field>
		<field id="9" group="9" type="i:gap" mode="0">
			<answer correct="true">went </answer>
		</field>
		<field id="10" group="10" type="i:gap" mode="0">
			<answer correct="true">entertained </answer>
		</field>
		<field id="11" group="11" type="i:gap" mode="0">
			<answer correct="true">played </answer>
		</field>
		<field id="12" group="12" type="i:gap" mode="0">
			<answer correct="true">walked </answer>
		</field>
